James Abraham, Jos Three women have been confirmed dead after they were shot by gunmen in Vatt community, Barkin Ladi Council Area of Plateau State. A youth leader in the community, Dalyop Solomon, told our correspondent in Jos on Tuesday that the women  were killed while  harvesting tomatoes on  their farms on Monday. He named the  deceased  as  Tabitha Joro Dung,  Ngo Yop Gwom Pam and Zong, adding that their corpses had been deposited at the mortuary. Solomon said, “Our people are mourning because suspected Fulani militias  invaded a tomatoes farm where local women were harvesting tomatoes  in  Vatt community. “As I talk with you, their corpses have been deposited in a mortuary. It’s really very sad.” He added that security officials, who visited the town,  had promised to fish out those behind the incident. Copyright PUNCH.
